column5: I can't wait to try these......just pray I don't loose them. Not spam...not affliated in any way....just heard awesome reviews.  http://www.316lurecompany.com/      Going to be awesome for some crazy top water pike/musky and night time bass fishing.  Jason
Nice!!  What size are those?  Whats the brand?
Wow don't want to lose one of those$$  Cool baits ....
those aint cheap either i just bought some soft bait minnows and 2 8 inch rising sons in shad and hitch cant wait to test those babys out
Only just saw the link now. WOW  I would bring a snorkle and goggles fishing with those.  I would love to have a few of those in the box.

Thank God they float.....some 80lb braid and leader material going on those before they even see water.  I do believe I need help.....I'm going to be divorced before I get married if the fiancee finds out the cost on those
not many lures that will make me say holy *#&% F(@^%!@ C(#)@# But that is a first, good luck on em
ill stick with my 3.99 fin S fish for most of my fishing lol..
Wow...those are SWEET looking....taking them up north with you I assume???
Wow those are gorgeous... definitely cause for a divorce though!!!! hmmmm should I get a couple.... hahaha
Ya those are purdy, I could never see myself spending that kind of money on a lure.  Perhaps you should call your insurance company and see if you can get them insured.
Cool looking baits! But then if I was a fish I would have been caught a millions times by now!
Now that was funny  .  They look great Jason, looking forward to seeing the results.

ARE YOU SERIOUS!!!!! THOSE PRICES ARE A JOKE RIGHT?!?!?!?!?! WOW!!!!! THOSE THINGS BETTER CATCH YOU THE MOST AND BIGGEST FISH EVER!!!!!  I have to bookmark that page, cause my dad will never believe me that i saw a fishing lure worth $80! HOLY F***
Ya they are expensive, but i guess if u got the $$. Have fun with em hope to see some nice fish with those.
